         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8/8/60. ¶ My dear Dr Wilkie ¶  ¶ On the noticepaper of the Royal Society I observe, that an additional supply of stores is to be considered. ¶  ¶ Having heard, that it is contemplated to have dried be...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.08.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To David Wilkie</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 13071 Royal Society of Victoria Exploration Committee records, box 2077/5, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/8/60.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Dr Wilkie</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the noticepaper of the Royal Society I observe, that an additional supply of stores is to be considered.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. for the Burke &amp; Wills exploring expedition.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Having heard, that it is contemplated to have dried beef prepared in Melbourne to a great amount, I would beg to suggest, that instead of it flour should be taken, which is the most essential article of food.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It appears to me a pity to carry up to the Darling<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Darling River, NSW.</p>
               </note> meat, which can be obtained at a very cheap rate speedily in any quantity <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">there</hi>
               </seg>, by killing cattle &amp; drying the meat on the air, for which purpose the weather will be warm enough there in September.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I intended to have paid you a visit, but can seldom find a spare hour.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">your attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
